sec.p:
We performed a longitudinal assessment of 10 WT and 10 Lgals3−/− mice; we first tested mice at 2–3 months old, followed by repeat assessment at 6–7 months old. Investigators were not blinded to mouse genotype. Mice were assigned to calorimetry enclosures in a random manner. Animals were fasted overnight, then placed into 8 hermetically-sealed metabolic cages (Oxymax, Columbus Instruments). Mice were tested between 10:00 and 17:00; each measurement of gas tension required 2 min, so each animal had its metabolic parameters assessed every 16 min during the testing period. We used vendor supplied software (Oxymax for Windows 4.49) to determine maximum oxygen uptake (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
